# Performance & Accessibility Standards

## Performance Requirements
- Page load time must be under 2 seconds
- API responses must be under 500ms
- Implement proper loading states and skeleton screens
- Use Next.js Image component for optimized images
- Implement code splitting and lazy loading
- Leverage Next.js built-in caching mechanisms

## Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA Compliance)
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Implement proper ARIA labels and roles
- Ensure keyboard navigation works for all interactive elements
- Maintain proper color contrast ratios (4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text)
- Provide alt text for images
- Ensure focus indicators are visible
- Support screen readers with proper markup

## Responsive Design
- Mobile-first approach using Tailwind breakpoints
- Test on multiple device sizes (mobile, tablet, desktop)
- Implement touch-friendly interactions (minimum 44px touch targets)
- Ensure text remains readable on all screen sizes
- Use CSS Grid and Flexbox through Tailwind classes

## Offline Functionality
- Use IndexedDB for offline data storage
- Implement sync mechanisms when online
- Provide clear offline/online status indicators
- Handle conflicts when syncing data
- Cache critical resources for offline use

## Monitoring
- Implement Web Vitals monitoring
- Track Core Web Vitals (LCP, FID, CLS)
- Monitor bundle sizes and performance metrics
- Set up alerts for performance degradation